### Lower Bound on the Gap Function

We begin the convergence analysis by demonstrating a lower bound on \(\mathrm{Gap}(\bm{w}_{i},\widehat{\bm{p}}_{i})\).

**Lemma 3.2** (Gap Lower Bound).: _Under the setting in which Lemma 2.5 holds, for all \(\bm{w}\in\mathcal{B}(2\|\bm{w}^{*}\|_{2})\), \(\mathrm{Gap}(\bm{w},\widehat{\bm{p}})\geq-\frac{12\beta^{2}B}{c_{1}}\widehat{ \mathrm{OPT}}+\frac{c_{1}}{2}\|\bm{w}-\bm{w}^{*}\|_{2}^{2}+\nu D_{\phi}( \widehat{\bm{p}}^{*},\widehat{\bm{p}})\)._

Proof.: Writing \((\sigma(\bm{w}\cdot\bm{x})-y)^{2}=\big{(}(\sigma(\bm{w}\cdot\bm{x})-\sigma( \bm{w}^{*}\cdot\bm{x}))+(\sigma(\bm{w}^{*}\cdot\bm{x})-y)\big{)}^{2}\) and expanding the square, we have

\[L(\bm{w},\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*})-L(\bm{w}^{*},\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*} )=\mathbb{E}_{(\bm{x},y)\sim\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*}}[(\sigma(\bm{w}\cdot\bm{x})-y )^{2}-(\sigma(\bm{w}^{*}\cdot\bm{x})-y)^{2}]\] \[= -2\mathbb{E}_{\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*}}[(\sigma(\bm{w}^{*}\cdot\bm{x} )-y)(\sigma(\bm{w}\cdot\bm{x})-\sigma(\bm{w}^{*}\cdot\bm{x}))]+\mathbb{E}_{ \widehat{\bm{p}}^{*}}[((\sigma(\bm{w}\cdot\bm{x})-\sigma(\bm{w}^{*}\cdot\bm{ x}))^{2}].\]

By the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality, we further have that

\[\mathbb{E}_{\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*}}[(\sigma(\bm{w}^{*}\cdot\bm{x}) -y)(\sigma(\bm{w}\cdot\bm{x})-\sigma(\bm{w}^{*}\cdot\bm{x}))]\] \[\leq\sqrt{\mathbb{E}_{\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*}}[(\sigma(\bm{w}^{*} \cdot\bm{x})-y)^{2}]\mathbb{E}_{\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*}}[(\sigma(\bm{w}\cdot\bm {x})-\sigma(\bm{w}^{*}\cdot\bm{x}))^{2}]}\] \[\leq\beta\sqrt{6B}\sqrt{\widehat{\mathrm{OPT}}}\|\bm{w}-\bm{w}^{*} \|_{2},\] (11)

