On the other hand, by the left inequality in Equation (5), we also have

\[\mathbb{E}_{\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*}}[(\sigma(\bm{w}\cdot\bm{x})-\sigma(\bm{w}^{*} \cdot\bm{x}))^{2}]\geq c_{1}\|\bm{w}-\bm{w}^{*}\|_{2}^{2}.\] (12)

Thus, combining Equation (3.2) and Equation (12), we get

\[L(\bm{w},\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*})-L(\bm{w}^{*},\widehat{\bm{p}}^{*}) \geq-2\beta\sqrt{6B}\|\bm{w}-\bm{w}^{*}\|_{2}\sqrt{\widehat{ \mathrm{OPT}}}+c_{1}\|\bm{w}-\bm{w}^{*}\|_{2}^{2}\] \[\geq-\frac{12\beta^{2}B}{c_{1}}\widehat{\mathrm{OPT}}+\frac{c_{1} }{2}\|\bm{w}-\bm{w}^{*}\|_{2}^{2},\] (13)

