## Appendix D Gap Upper Bound

To prove Lemma 3.3, we need to construct an upper bound on the gap \(\mathrm{Gap}(\bm{w}_{i},\widehat{\bm{p}}_{i})=L(\bm{w}_{i},\widehat{\bm{p}}^{ \,*})-L(\bm{w}^{*},\widehat{\bm{p}}_{i})\). To achieve this, we establish an upper bound on \(L(\bm{w}_{i},\widehat{\bm{p}}^{\,*})\), which motivates the update rule for \(\widehat{\bm{p}}_{i}\). We also establish a lower bound on \(L(\bm{w}^{*},\widehat{\bm{p}}_{i})\), which guides the update rule for \(\bm{w}_{i}\) and the construction of \(\bm{g}_{i}\). Note that the construction of the lower bound is more challenging here, due to the nonconvexity of the square loss. This is where most of the (non-standard) technical work happens. To simplify the notation, we use \(\phi(\widehat{\bm{p}}):=\chi^{2}(\widehat{\bm{p}},\widehat{\bm{p}}_{0})\) throughout this section.

